"```sql\nSELECT d.district_id, \n       ((d.A13 - d.A12) / d.A12) * 100 AS unemployment_increment_rate\nFROM loan l\nJOIN account a ON l.account_id = a.account_id\nJOIN disp di ON a.account_id = di.account_id\nJOIN client c ON di.client_id = c.client_id\nJOIN district d ON c.district_id = d.district_id\nWHERE l.status = 'D' \n  AND l.date IS NOT NULL;  -- Assuming we want to filter out loans that have a valid date\n``` \n\nThis SQL query selects the district ID and calculates the percentage increment in the unemployment rate from 1995 to 1996 for loans that are still running and where the client is in debt. It joins the necessary tables based on the foreign key relationships defined in the schema."